               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the donor; incipit of Texts I-II; titles of the books to be read; numbers and initial words of Psalms to be read; in some nomina sacra, some separate letters (alternating with black letters) (e.g. fols. 4v, 5v, 6r); directives to the ministers; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals; quire marks.&#xD;
On the incipit page of Text I (fol.3r), a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="64v"/>Fol. 64v l. 12: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ እሞሆይ[sic]፡ ወለተ፡ ኪዳን፡ ዘወሀበቶ፡ ለታቦተ፡ ቅዱሰ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ቀርሰበር፡ ከመ፡ ይኩና፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ስመ፡ [fol. 65r] አቡሃ፡ ገብ{ረ}፡ ሐዋርያ፡ ወእማ፡ ወለተ፡ መድኅን፡ ወስመ፡ ውሉዳ፡ ሃይለ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዐፀደ፡ ማርያም፡ ክንፈ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ተጽሕፈ፡ በ፲፻ወ፱፻፸፡ አመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ውጉዝ፡ ውእቱ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጳጳስ፡ አባ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ለጸሐፊሁ፡ ገብረ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ወስመ፡ አኃዊሃ፡ ገብረ፡ ትንሣኤ፡ ገብረ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ገብረ፡ ሊባኖስ፡ ሃይለ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለተ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወለተ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።<foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>ʾƎmmahoy Wälättä Kidan is referred to as the donor of the Ms. Her relatives are also mentioned: her father Gäbrä Ḥawarya, her mother Wälättä Mädḫǝn, her sons Haylä Mikaʾel, ʿAḍädä Maryam and Kǝnfä Mikaʾel, and her brothers and sisters. Besides, the colophon mentions the date 1970 A.M. (= 1977/78 A.D.) of the completion of the manuscript, and Täklä Haymanot, the Patriarch of Ethiopia from 1976 to 1988, here called ṗaṗas.</note>
                     </colophon>
